Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.29,0:00:03.22,sign_7_1_Class_3_2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(600,1)}Class 3-2
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.60,0:00:08.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hide somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.47,0:00:18.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I have to wake up... I have to wake up soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.59,0:00:20.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Or they'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.65,0:00:44.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Ryo?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.11,0:00:46.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.02,0:00:48.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It found me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.26,0:00:52.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, I'm finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:25.08,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,400)}October 8th \N Nocturnal Community Relations Division
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.99,0:02:25.58,sign_3405_9_Storage__1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Storage #1
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.80,0:02:30.26,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck, where did it go?\N Where could it have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.08,0:02:32.08,Ep_Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,550)}#9 "The Dream Demon of\N the Haunted Apartment Block"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:32.73,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako, are you almost done?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.73,0:02:34.47,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, just give me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:37.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you doing, Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.89,0:02:43.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you guys know what happened\N to that budget request I made?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.06,0:02:46.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The one you met with the other sections about,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:49.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and even got the bureau director's stamp on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:52.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! The one that took me a whole week.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.79,0:02:55.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did you lose it during our\N last paperwork cleanup?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.90,0:03:01.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No! I have to go through that\N whole stamp rally again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.93,0:03:04.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you look, Theo-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.07,0:03:07.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.11,0:03:09.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a great co-worker!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.10,0:03:10.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.77,0:03:12.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We have an urgent job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.90,0:03:13.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:15.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Urgent?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:17.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,From Koharu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:25.26,sign_4728_30_Subject__Sakaki_,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs16}Subject: Sakaki-kun, Urgent Request\N To: Sakaki Kyoichi\N From: Senda Reiji\N {\fs18}Aida Koharu-san from General Affairs has a kid who's involved in \Nsome kind of Another-related trouble. Please talk to her. \NIt seems like her kid is having nightmares and can't sleep at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.72,0:03:18.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Koharu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:21.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She works here in our building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.57,0:03:25.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Her kid's having nightmares?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.26,0:03:28.31,sign_4728_30_Subject__Sakaki_,,0000,0000,0000,,Aida-san is working late tonight \Nand will be at Café L’ambre at 19:00. \NI can't go because I've got a social function, \Nso somebody go get the details and fill me in later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:28.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't you usually go to a hospital for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.63,0:03:32.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Senda-san sent it to us because he\N assumed that would be the wrong move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.65,0:03:34.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So this is our priority for the day—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.85,0:03:38.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No! That budget sheet is a priority!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:39.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.27,0:03:43.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako, want to go alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.31,0:03:46.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.45,0:03:47.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:49.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't do anything on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:53.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give Aida-san a call,\Nso you can go talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.57,0:03:54.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:03:59.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on it. I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.01,0:04:08.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We saw something like this before, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.48,0:04:09.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.90,0:04:13.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It was worse in Nerima and Ota\N Wards than here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.66,0:04:15.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.64,0:04:18.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If it's happened before,\N it's easier to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.60,0:04:22.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And it's about time for him to start gaining\N some confidence in his work, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.70,0:04:25.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you're capable of being that considerate,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.52,0:04:30.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,why did you boss him around\N like that during the Azazel thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.93,0:04:35.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I already said I feel bad about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:38.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I underestimated him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.69,0:04:42.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think he'd refuse my apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:45.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'm in debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.69,0:04:47.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you really feel that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.29,0:04:51.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then be a good senpai and pay him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.22,0:04:54.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.87,0:05:09.64,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,So, how much have you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.64,0:05:13.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It has to do with dreams, and involves\N our department. That's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.88,0:05:14.88,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.71,0:05:19.10,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I have two boys, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:22.54,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The younger one's name is Ryo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.54,0:05:26.30,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,His school called and told me\N he keeps napping in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:28.93,Flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I told you not to stay up all night, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:33.68,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I have these scary dreams...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.21,0:05:39.48,Flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Like the haunted house you went to\N with your dad over summer break?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.85,0:05:41.19,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.19,0:05:43.97,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But there's this monster that chases me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.55,0:05:47.82,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And if it finds you three times, it eats you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.27,0:05:51.82,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It ate Acchan and Yo-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.31,0:05:56.46,Flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Those are your friends who've been\N absent with a cold for a long time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:58.10,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm next!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.78,0:06:02.28,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It found me twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.53,0:06:09.31,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,So two of his friends had the same\N dream and stopped coming to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.31,0:06:10.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Dreams...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:14.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I explained that being hurt in dreams\N doesn't hurt you in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:18.68,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But several days later, Ryo didn't wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:21.70,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,And he still hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.08,0:06:25.73,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The hospital says they can't\N find anything wrong with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.08,0:06:29.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why you haven't been to work lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.43,0:06:31.28,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.67,0:06:35.49,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,When I told Senda-san about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:39.50,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.72,0:06:44.33,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's a job for Nocturnal\NCommunity Relations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.33,0:06:46.74,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Not a normal doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:50.66,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to my staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.17,0:06:52.84,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be in touch soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.49,0:06:59.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, I'd forgotten that Nocturnal\N Community Relations handles this stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.25,0:07:01.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd remembered sooner—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.02,0:07:02.08,Default - Top,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:05.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do what we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.28,0:07:09.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.77,0:07:12.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So we start with gathering information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.01,0:07:14.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.33,0:07:17.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Any idea what Another it is, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.11,0:07:18.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, none yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.43,0:07:22.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Log into A-Search and search for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.86,0:07:24.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You may be able to narrow it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:25.67,sign_10669_103_Another_Search_S,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Another Search System
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.03,0:07:27.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Dreams...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:30.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,"Dream demons"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.58,0:07:33.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They give you nightmares, and\N swallow you up into nightmares...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.10,0:07:35.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There're lots of different Anothers, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.00,0:07:38.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Evening, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.96,0:07:41.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you're {\i1}still{\i0} looking\N for that document?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.70,0:07:42.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.55,0:07:44.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, what do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.42,0:07:45.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Miyako-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.76,0:07:47.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:49.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.10,0:07:50.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I have a message for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.75,0:07:56.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That party will be held again this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:07:58.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.71,0:08:01.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, we and the other wards take turns
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.78,0:08:03.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,temporarily transferring someone to\Nthe Tokyo Metropolitan Government Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.14,0:08:05.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Transferring?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.48,0:08:07.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We work for one of the special wards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:09.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo Metropolitan Government Office\Nemployees are Tokyo city employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.62,0:08:11.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:15.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So every year, each ward sends one person\N to work with the city government for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.13,0:08:19.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The goal is to build relationships between\N the wards and the city government.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.72,0:08:22.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And so... This year, it's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I've got that urgent job...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.01,0:08:30.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. Sharing that with\N them is part of what this is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.99,0:08:32.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it starts tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.54,0:08:42.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.53,0:08:45.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:48.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shimizu, from Chiyoda Ward!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:08:50.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We saw each other at Toyama Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.35,0:08:52.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:55.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, how do you remember my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:08:59.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're famous for a lot of\N reasons in our business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:03.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You've been really busy\N ever since then, I've heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:09.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. I've heard about \Nyou as well, Miyako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.59,0:09:12.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.88,0:09:18.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kanoichi Satoru, with the Tokyo Metropolitan \NNocturnal Cultural and Environmental Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.83,0:09:22.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoichi? Are you related to Kanoichi Akane?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:25.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, she and I are cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.64,0:09:28.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.52,0:09:30.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako Arata-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.03,0:09:37.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Really? You're willing to help us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:40.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That's how this works.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.55,0:09:42.56,sign_3369_5_July_24th__Shinj,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,400)}October 9th
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.48,0:09:43.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you think, from the look if it, that\N the Another can be eliminated,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.11,0:09:44.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.75,0:09:46.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminated?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.19,0:09:48.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Your department has the same equipment, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:09:53.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So this is a dream demon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.12,0:09:55.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The same one that showed up\N in Nerima Ward before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:09:56.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Before?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:09:59.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It keeps happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.96,0:10:02.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A child goes into a building\N that nobody uses anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:05.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,thanks to the decreasing population, \Nand goes into a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.41,0:10:10.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There are tons of spots even in\N downtown Tokyo that are abandoned,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.35,0:10:13.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,due to land prices and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.81,0:10:18.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The spots are always places\N where there used to be children,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.09,0:10:20.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,like hospitals or elementary schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.54,0:10:27.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.68,0:10:32.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I was just wondering why\Nthe victims are always children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.77,0:10:35.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.69,0:10:40.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've never thought about\N why Anothers do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.08,0:10:47.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, we can use legends and\N traditions to guess at their motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:51.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we lack your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.73,0:10:53.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Ears of Sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.47,0:10:57.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,An ability that allows you to\N communicate with Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.13,0:11:00.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.69,0:11:04.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And we don't think we need it, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.30,0:11:08.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're going to co-exist,\N isn't it better if you can communicate?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.94,0:11:12.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If I can exterminate an Another, I will,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.40,0:11:14.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and if I can't, I'll treat it as\N a form of natural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.60,0:11:17.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you talk with rats or typhoons?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:19.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Rats?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.17,0:11:24.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Anothers have always had reasons for\N what they've done in all the cases I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.80,0:11:28.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of them I couldn't\N accept or understand, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:32.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Nocturnal Community\N Relations sections are, in theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:35.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,supposed to find a way to\N co-exist with Anothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.61,0:11:38.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't communicate with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:41.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've been able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.79,0:11:45.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.12,0:11:47.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.77,0:11:51.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going to get anywhere like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.33,0:11:53.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:58.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to talk to people\N involved in the case, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.15,0:12:03.16,sign_6555_61_April_6th___Shin,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,400)}October 9th
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.15,0:12:03.64,sign_17243_190_JR_Shinjuku_Stat,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,JR Shinjuku Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.31,0:12:06.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell us what you know, Kakeru-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.82,0:12:07.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:11.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It was a rumor in Ryo's class...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:14.17,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm playing tag in my dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:15.84,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:18.18,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've been caught twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:19.93,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, I'll win!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.93,0:12:22.63,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\N It's just a dream, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:25.00,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I gotta win, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.76,0:12:30.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,After that, his friend \Nstopped going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:33.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the rumors started to spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.90,0:12:36.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,About how if you get caught\N three times, you don't wake up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.34,0:12:40.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,My little brother said that\N before he went into a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:43.71,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It found me twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.55,0:12:47.15,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Acchan and Yo-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.15,0:12:49.53,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Are you dreaming about playing tag?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.23,0:12:53.54,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yo-kun said he started having dreams\N after Acchan stopped coming to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.99,0:12:56.35,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was having the same dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.35,0:12:59.54,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd dreamed about playing tag twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:02.92,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the next day he stopped\N coming to school, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.16,0:13:07.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right after that, Ryo went into a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:11.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How did Ryo-kun know it was the same dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.10,0:13:16.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The game always starts\N in the same place, he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.88,0:13:20.19,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It always... starts in the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.52,0:13:22.53,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The apartment block we used to play in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:24.29,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Ghost Apartments.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.29,0:13:26.50,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He made the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:29.57,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We all dream of that place!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:31.28,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So it's the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.28,0:13:35.08,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Which means... Which means\N the same thing will happen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:37.26,Flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It'll eat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.27,0:13:41.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to happen to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.81,0:13:47.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me about these Ghost Apartments.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.67,0:13:50.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's an old apartment \Ncomplex near our school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:53.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Ryo used to play there with his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.47,0:13:56.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That matches what we know\N about the dream demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.25,0:13:57.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.14,0:14:02.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Please... promise me you'll save my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.12,0:14:03.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we're on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.73,0:14:07.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.10,0:14:11.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,First, tell us where these apartments are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.27,0:14:12.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.15,0:14:15.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.51,0:14:17.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is building 28, which is no longer used,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.79,0:14:19.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and where they used to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.85,0:14:23.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this feels different from the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.00,0:14:26.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start by going inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.23,0:14:29.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you show us what you can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.02,0:14:34.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This was originally a Shinjuku Ward case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.76,0:14:38.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you investigate the building?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:40.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll put up a barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.51,0:14:44.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you're worried, I'll back you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.41,0:14:48.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.32,0:14:50.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.68,0:14:54.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoichi-san, need some tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.07,0:14:57.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No, I have my own methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.70,0:14:59.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.04,0:15:00.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Miyako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.56,0:15:02.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Call me if something comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:07.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, time to get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.87,0:15:16.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.63,0:15:19.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:30.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's better than the basement \Nunder Mount Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.22,0:15:38.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tag! Tag!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.53,0:15:41.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tag! Tag!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:40.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.94,0:15:44.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.07,0:15:48.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:50.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tag! Tag!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.71,0:15:52.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play! Let's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.34,0:16:03.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:05.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't tag. It's hide-and-seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.03,0:16:09.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You can hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:10.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.82,0:16:13.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one who kidnapped\N Ryo-kun and the other kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.69,0:16:16.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't kidnap them. I had them join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:17.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.60,0:16:20.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Tag!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.26,0:16:20.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.68,0:16:23.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we're not done talking yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.36,0:16:25.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.41,0:16:28.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.43,0:16:29.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.81,0:16:30.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:34.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.47,0:16:39.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.17,0:16:42.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Are you in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.79,0:16:43.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.81,0:16:46.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a MegaTrive!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.26,0:16:47.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I remember this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.52,0:16:49.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.50,0:16:51.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.63,0:16:55.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.50,0:16:58.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.01,0:17:00.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:06.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,In this world, nobody can see me.\N So I can't play with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:08.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I can do what I want in their dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:14.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We play three games.\N If I win three times, they're mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.96,0:17:16.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.83,0:17:20.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Since you can't get them\N to play with you in reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.14,0:17:23.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,you're having them play with you in dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.33,0:17:27.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There used to be lots of people\N here until a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.45,0:17:30.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:31.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I could always play.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:36.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're gone now, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.15,0:17:39.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody left. And I stayed here, alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.42,0:17:44.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But then, kids came that I could play with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.87,0:17:46.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So I had them join me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:48.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Now I won't be lonely!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.81,0:17:51.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:53.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.06,0:17:58.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Lately I haven't been able\N to play with any of my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:01.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're lonely?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.63,0:18:02.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A little.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.14,0:18:05.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So I promised I'd play with them soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.69,0:18:07.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.64,0:18:11.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes your friends\N have to go away for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.34,0:18:13.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I think you're still connected to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:16.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So don't force people to be your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.53,0:18:19.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for people who will play with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.85,0:18:21.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.09,0:18:27.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Arata.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:29.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Ara... ta?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.74,0:18:33.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If this place is lonely for you,\N go someplace with more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.35,0:18:37.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you to a place with lots of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.23,0:18:40.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A place where I won't be lonely?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:44.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is there one? Can I go there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:48.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you take me to a place where\N I won't be lonely, I'll give everyone back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:51.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're lying, I'll trap you in a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.57,0:18:55.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, there's no need to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:57.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We can talk, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.78,0:19:00.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So if you want to complain to me, you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:02.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it means to be friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.92,0:19:03.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.55,0:19:06.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:09.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's get going, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.20,0:19:11.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.08,0:19:15.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.12,0:19:17.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miyako-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:21.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've been looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.08,0:19:22.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:25.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So, is this the Another?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:27.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:30.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It seems it was kidnapping\N children out of loneliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:36.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.81,0:19:39.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then he's my friend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.05,0:19:41.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's do it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.86,0:19:49.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kanoichi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:19:58.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There, it's dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.59,0:20:05.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! One stomp with your foot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.25,0:20:08.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,People who work at the Metropolitan\NGovernment Office really are amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.87,0:20:10.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:14.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous if you're not used to it,\N though. So don't try and copy me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.51,0:20:16.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Were you okay, Miyako-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.02,0:20:21.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.21,0:20:23.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I dealt with the Another.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.37,0:20:26.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd release the children!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.85,0:20:29.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're a naïve idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.96,0:20:34.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's assume, hypothetically,\N that he released the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.04,0:20:38.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What guarantee do we have\N that he wouldn't do it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:40.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:46.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What you're doing is the same\N as killing a criminal who confesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.04,0:20:49.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and saying that you've gotten rid of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:51.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anothers are things, not people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.77,0:20:54.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They're stories that have\N stopped midway, you could say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.95,0:20:57.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They repeat the same actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.11,0:20:59.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Our only option is to eliminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.63,0:21:00.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminate them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.70,0:21:03.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And I can't trust your interpreting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.04,0:21:06.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying the Ears of Sand are a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.46,0:21:07.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.45,0:21:09.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard a lot of stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.42,0:21:14.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,One, for instance, about a terrible\N Another that calls itself your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.34,0:21:19.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there's even\N a chance that you're trying to trick us
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:22.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and bring chaos to society.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:28.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... as a servant of the god of\N chaos and deception, Huehuecóyotl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:32.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You know that he's the destroyer \Nof civilization, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.04,0:21:35.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying you can't trust me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.15,0:21:43.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? You don't think people think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.07,0:21:46.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You've never given it a second thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.91,0:21:50.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the people around \Nyou really do spoil you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.01,0:21:52.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.84,0:21:55.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're not needed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.83,0:21:59.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's{\i0} what I'm saying,  Miyako Arata-san.
